condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Article III. 3.03 (a) | Description :The recipient shall cause each participating State to require itsrespective CSDA to deposit into its CSDA Project Account an initial amount of at least N150 million | Due Date :31-Oct-2014

Finance Agreement :Article III. 3.03 (b) | Description :The recipient shall cause each participating State to require itsrespective CSDA to replenish its CSDA Project Account by the first day of each calendar semester with an amount of at least N25million | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Article IV. 4.01. (a) | Description :At least one Subsidiary Agreement has been executed on behalf of theRecipient and one Participating State, in form and substance satisfactory to the Association (Effectiveness Condition) | Due Date:28-Nov-2014

Finance Agreement :Article IV. 4.01. (b) | Description :The Recipient, through the Federal Ministry of Finance, has restructuredthe Federal Project Support Unit, in form and substance satisfactory to the Association (Effectiveness Condition) | Due Date:28-Nov-2014

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, E, 5 | Description :The Recipient shall cause the North East States to ensure that anyarea in which civil works under the Project will be implemented has been cleared of Explosive Remnants of War and the Recipientshall provide a confirmation, in form and substance satisfactory to the Association, that this area has been declared safe andclear of Explosive Remnants of War. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II, A, 2, (a) | Description :The Recipient shall, not later than six (6) months followingthe Effective Date appoint third party monitoring agent(s) for the Project under terms of reference, and with qualifications andexperience satisfactory to the Association. | Due Date :28-Feb-2017

Finance Agreement :Section I. A. 1. | Description :Recipient established FPSU and thereafter maintain it at all times during theProject Implementation period, with qualified and experienced staff. | Due Date :18-Dec-2009
Finance Agreement :Section I. A. 4. | Description :Recipient also cause States to establish and maintain CSDAs under relevant lawsand provisions acceptable to the Association. | Due Date :18-Dec-2009
Finance Agreement :Section I. C. 1 | Description :Community grants are to be made under terms and conditions acceptable to IDA |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Section I. F. 1 (a) | Description :The Recipient shall, no later than 9 months after Effectiveness Date, prepareand furnish to the Association for its review and approval, an operations manual which shall set forth detailed implementationarrangements for Part D of the project. | Due Date :28-Aug-2015

Finance Agreement :Section IV. B. 1 (b) (i) | Description :The recipient shall cause each participating Stste to deposit N100million in the account of the CSDA and at lest N50 million yearly for the relevant activities under the project. | Due Date:18-Dec-2009

Finance Agreement :Section IV. B. 1. (b) | Description :Notwithstanding the provisions of Part A of this Section, no withdrawalshall be made for payments under any Category to be made with respect to any Participating State until the Recipient has furnishedto the Association evidence satisfactory to the Association that eligibility criteria have been fulfilled. (Disbursement Condition)| Due Date :20-Nov-2015

Finance Agreement :Section IV. B. 1. (c) | Description :Notwithstanding the provisions of Part A of this Section, no withdrawalshall be made for payments under Category (4) unless and until the Recipient has adopted the VG Manual in the form, substance andmanner satisfactory to the Association. (Disbursement Condition) | Due Date :20-Nov-2015

Finance Agreement :Section IV. B. 1. (d) | Description :Notwithstanding the provisions of Part A of this Section, no withdrawalshall be made for payments under Category (1) until the Recipient has furnished to the Association evidence satisfactory to theAssociation that it has deposited in the FPSU Project Account an initial deposit in the amount of at least fifty million Naira(N50,000,000). (Disbursement Condition) | Due Date :27-Feb-2015
